column34: In light of the evidence that’s been shown of Amber Heard admitting she abused Johnny Depp, I feel that it’s only right that she lose her part as Mera in the next Aquaman movie. As Johnny Depp lost his role as Captain Jack Sparrow in Pirates of the Caribbean due to her abuse allegations. Johnny lost a role he cherished and put EVERYTHING into due to basic allegations with zero evidence, while Amber Heard has been able to maintain her role as Mera in Aquaman even though evidence has been brought into the light with her ADMITTING she abused him. I ask that you sing this petition and make our voices heard that we do NOT condone abuse from ANYONE. #JusticeforJohnny.

column2:
Ms Heard claimed to have donated millions of her divorce settlement to two charities. Subsequent court proceedings indicate that years later they have not received any donations from her. Charities rely on people making good on their pledge so that they can help those that are less fortunate. She pledged $3.5m to each charity, a total of $7m.

- I will no longer support any charity or cause Ms Heard is an ambassador of. (Apologies to the charities but you will need to find more appropriate advocates or ambassadors).

- I will no longer buy or support any product Ms Heard is promoting, paid or otherwise. Including employment in any capacity she has in any aspect within the media, particularly the movie industry. 

- Her performance as “Mera”, to be blunt, sucked. I hope they find a better actress if only to have a more believable character as well as easier dialogue with other actors (I felt bad for Mamoa, she ruined Aquaman for him).

column2: Women can also be abusive. Everything I’ve read about this case points to narcissistic abuse from Ms. Heard. The fact that Mr. Depp’s mental health history is being attacked as a means to “prove” he is “abusive“ is disgusting. That is what narcissists do; learn your vulnerabilities so they can exploit, hurt and destroy you. Her behaviour sets back progress for women who are actually victims of domestic violence. Why is it necessary for her attorneys to focus on Mr. Depp’s mental health history?? From what I have read in several articles, the case against Mr. Depp lacks actual evidence, and is mostly Ms. Heard and her attorneys attacking Mr. Depp and his mental health. Mental health also includes addiction, and that does not make someone a bad or abusive person. Also, why is she outside court posing and smiling?? Her behaviour is not consistent with being an actual victim. When you dig up real abuse, it’s nothing to smile about. Narcissists also provoke their victims and encourage them to engage in unhealthy behaviour; to which Mr. Depp stated Ms. Heard did so in setting up lines of cocaine for him. This is disgusting, that someone could be openly abused in public. You know, actual abuse. She is given women, and bisexual women a bad and false portrait. She does not deserve fame to further fuel her abusive behaviour. Even if her ex wife/girlfriend (unsure of specifics) claims the allegations of domestic abuse were false; a narcissist is great at manipulation, and could easily have convinces a victim that her behaviour was not abuse. Furthermore, Ms. Heard is said to still be close to her ex wife and they are friends. Narcissists try to keep their ex’s close to further exploit and use them. An officer who previously arrested Ms. Heard, is herself a lesbian activist. So, Ms. Heard was not a “victim” of misogyny or homophobia when she was arrested for domestic violence. I do not know either party, but I am very aware of human behaviour; and her behaviour (words and actions) do resemble that of an overt narcissist and sociopath, to which a family counsellor for the couple had diagnosed. Mr. Depp’s work as an actor should not be diminished because of a narcissist. His character should not be defamed by a narcissist who is after all, an excellent actor. If you evaluate both parties’ words and behaviour, a more accurate portrait is displayed. Why does Ms. Heard and her attorneys’ feel the need to focus on mental health history, rather than actual evidence? Because there is no evidence. Hazy photos of cocaine and a man passed out are not evidence. I hope the court looks at actual evidence, and her attorneys’ unethical attempts to focus on and attack Mr. Depp’s mental health. Ms. Heard should not be rewarded with a high profile part in a movie that children and families will likely endorse. What message would that send? Please stop attacking people for their mental health history, including a history of addiction. ✌�
